CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1952, pg. 3 reads: "Favorite Church Woman Entries...Among the first entries in "Favorite Church Woman" contest entries are these three outstanding leaders. Left to right: Mrs. L.J. Christian, Miller Street Church of God in Christ... Rules governing the contest can be found elsewhere in this paper. - Harris and Sockwell Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. L.J. Christian wearing satin dress with upturned cuffs and round brooch, and woven hat, posed in domestic interior with leaf patterned sofa
